OL,3,CEnergy price cap to rise unexpectedly
OL,4,Cin January, Ofgem says
OL,6,FFrom January to March, a typical dual-
OL,7,Ffuel household will pay #1,758 a year,
OL,8,Fup from the current #1,755 cap, an
OL,9,Fincrease of about 28p a month.
OL,11,FWholesale prices, which make up the
OL,12,Flargest share of the cap, have fallen
OL,13,F4% over the past three months but
OL,14,Fremain volatile due to global events.
OL,16,FThe cap sets the maximum price
OL,17,Fsuppliers can charge per unit of gas
OL,18,Fand electricity, not the total bill,
OL,19,Fso households that use more energy
OL,20,Fwill pay more.
